contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:05.841 --> 02:08.576
<i>One of the toughest tasks</i>
<i>in intelligence work</i>

02:08.644 --> 02:10.745
<i>is learning how to wait.</i>

02:10.812 --> 02:12.714
<i>When meeting an operative</i>
<i>in public,</i>

02:12.781 --> 02:14.248
<i>you have to be</i>
<i>on constant alert</i>

02:14.316 --> 02:17.552
<i>for undercover law enforcement</i>
<i>and surveillance.</i>

02:17.620 --> 02:19.454
<i>But when anyone</i>
<i>could be your enemy,</i>

02:19.521 --> 02:21.422
<i>it's hard to act natural.</i>

02:26.028 --> 02:27.996
Michael:
Is that book any good?

02:28.063 --> 02:29.931
I've been meaning
to read it.

02:29.999 --> 02:33.201
There are no spies in it.
That's a plus.

02:33.268 --> 02:35.737
[ Children playing ]

02:38.107 --> 02:41.476
I used to bring you and Nate
here when you were little.

02:41.543 --> 02:42.910
He loved the swings.

02:42.978 --> 02:45.246
You couldn't pay him
to get off of them.

02:45.314 --> 02:46.447
Remember?

02:46.515 --> 02:48.082
My arms still hurt
from pushing him.

02:48.150 --> 02:49.717
Eyes forward, Mom.

02:49.785 --> 02:53.855
Remember, just two strangers
chatting in the park.

02:53.922 --> 02:56.591
It's all right.
Nobody followed me here.

02:56.659 --> 02:59.861
I bought a day at the spa,
I sneaked out the back,

02:59.928 --> 03:01.696
and just drove side streets
all the way.

03:01.764 --> 03:02.997
I'm clean.

03:03.065 --> 03:05.199
They're stepping up
the surveillance, Michael.

03:05.267 --> 03:06.668
You've got to
leave Miami.

03:06.735 --> 03:08.870
That's why I wanted to talk.
I need you to find Barry.

03:08.937 --> 03:14.375
You want me to reach out
to a mon-- a money launderer?

03:14.443 --> 03:16.177
Have you heard nothing
I've said?

03:16.245 --> 03:19.213
Riley's watching me all the time.
Please, Mom.

03:19.281 --> 03:21.416
Meet him in the ladies' room
of your lawyer's office

03:21.483 --> 03:22.550
if you have to,

03:22.618 --> 03:24.919
but I need him
to transfer money

03:24.987 --> 03:27.488
from our bank accounts
to these countries.

03:27.556 --> 03:29.724
[ Sighs ]

03:33.729 --> 03:36.731
Moldova...Nauru?

03:36.799 --> 03:38.066
Is that
where you're going?

03:38.133 --> 03:40.401
No, but the accounts
are flagged by the CIA

03:40.469 --> 03:42.270
and everyone they work with.

03:42.337 --> 03:44.205
If we do the transfers, they'll be
searching for us everywhere

03:44.273 --> 03:46.574
except where we're headed.

03:46.642 --> 03:48.276
Is this goodbye?

03:48.343 --> 03:51.212
It's close.
If you need me --

03:51.280 --> 03:52.346
Draw a green "X"
on the bus bench

03:52.414 --> 03:55.383
in Miami Beach --
I got it.

03:55.451 --> 03:56.684
[ Sniffles ]

03:56.752 --> 04:00.855
I know physical contact
isn't part of our cover...

04:00.923 --> 04:05.593
But you're the only family
I have left.

04:05.661 --> 04:06.894
If they catch us,
they catch us.

04:12.968 --> 04:14.202
Thank you, Mom,
for everything.

04:23.112 --> 04:25.379
Have a nice time
at the spa?

04:25.447 --> 04:28.149
What are you people
doing here?

04:28.217 --> 04:30.551
Just wanted to make sure your day was
as relaxing as you'd hoped it would be.

04:30.619 --> 04:33.254
You scheduled five hours' worth
of treatments, I understand.

04:33.322 --> 04:36.657
You were at the spa
that whole time?

04:36.725 --> 04:38.359
Of course I was.
[ Keys jingle ]

04:38.427 --> 04:40.595
Your men were following me --
just ask them.

04:40.662 --> 04:42.663
I did, and they told me
the same thing.

04:42.731 --> 04:44.065
Well, there you go.

04:44.133 --> 04:46.334
But I believe in
checking things out for myself,

04:46.401 --> 04:48.770
so I did some digging.

04:48.837 --> 04:51.105
That's from
southwest 27th Street.

04:51.173 --> 04:53.074
And that's you
behind the wheel.

04:53.142 --> 04:55.409
It's about five blocks
from the spa.

04:55.477 --> 04:56.878
It was taken an hour
into your appointment.

04:56.945 --> 04:59.113
I'd like to show you
something else.

04:59.181 --> 05:02.750
It's the agreement you signed
to be truthful and forthcoming

05:02.818 --> 05:05.319
with the agency,
under penalty of perjury.

05:05.387 --> 05:07.088
So, what happens now?

05:07.156 --> 05:09.290
Now? I'm done
playing games.

05:09.358 --> 05:11.626
Cuff her.

05:15.499 --> 05:18.999
<font color=#00FF00>Burn Notice 6x15</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Best Laid Plans</font>
Original Air Date on December 6, 2012

05:19.000 --> 05:22.500
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00FF00">elderman</font> ==

05:23.396 --> 05:25.348
<i>An interrogation</i>
<i>typically begins</i>

05:25.349 --> 05:27.504
<i>with deprivation</i>
<i>and discomfort.</i>

05:27.506 --> 05:30.241
<i>That means the thermostat</i>
<i>cranked all the way up,</i>

05:30.309 --> 05:32.343
<i>uncomfortable furniture,</i>

05:32.411 --> 05:34.412
<i>dim lights</i>
<i>that strain the eyes,</i>

05:34.479 --> 05:37.248
<i>and if there's food,</i>
<i>not much of it.</i>

05:37.316 --> 05:39.884
<i>It's all about making sure</i>
<i>you're exhausted and vulnerable</i>

05:39.951 --> 05:43.054
<i>before your interrogator</i>
<i>even sets foot in the door.</i>

05:43.121 --> 05:44.755
Riley: My goodness.

05:44.823 --> 05:47.858
Someone forgot to turn the
air conditioner on in here.

05:50.796 --> 05:52.263
I'm sorry
I've kept you waiting.

05:54.266 --> 05:56.267
[ Lighter clicks ]

05:59.071 --> 06:00.504
I needed that.

06:00.572 --> 06:02.707
Do you know what the bit

06:02.774 --> 06:04.108
for an obstruction
of justice charge is?

06:04.176 --> 06:07.411
At your age,
you'll die in prison.

06:07.479 --> 06:10.548
Beats ending up
in a nursing home.

06:10.615 --> 06:12.616
I wouldn't be too sure
about that.

06:12.684 --> 06:14.919
You're helping
an enemy of the state.

06:14.986 --> 06:18.222
You're not gonna get sent to
some medium-security playground.

06:18.290 --> 06:20.558
You'll do hard time
the whole time.

06:20.625 --> 06:24.829
But tell us where your son is,
it doesn't have to be that way.

06:24.896 --> 06:27.898
The last I checked,
the CIA is not allowed

06:27.966 --> 06:30.201
to spy on
an American citizen,

06:30.268 --> 06:34.705
so I don't think I'd be
the only one in trouble here.

06:34.773 --> 06:37.108
You let me out now,
or I'll call my lawyer.

06:38.810 --> 06:39.844
[ Handcuffs rattle ]

06:39.911 --> 06:42.646
If you think
I would ever let you know

06:42.714 --> 06:45.383
where my son's gonna go,

06:45.450 --> 06:47.385
you're out
of your goddamn mind.

06:47.452 --> 06:49.153
<i>Going</i> to go?

06:50.922 --> 06:52.089
So, he's still in town?

06:57.763 --> 06:59.997
Thanks for all your help,
Mrs. Westen.

07:00.065 --> 07:01.899
Someone will be by
to see you out.

07:05.537 --> 07:07.338
[ Door closes ]

07:13.078 --> 07:15.646
Schmidt: Hey, I'm not trying
to get a fake I.D.

07:15.714 --> 07:17.181
so I can buy Zimas.

07:17.249 --> 07:19.650
No, you don't gouge
Calvin Schmidt.

07:19.718 --> 07:21.819
You -- are you laughing?

07:21.887 --> 07:23.554
Don't laugh at me!
Are you kidding?

07:23.622 --> 07:24.588
[ Knock on door ]

07:24.656 --> 07:27.024
[ Gun cocks ]

07:30.495 --> 07:31.796
Hey.

07:31.863 --> 07:34.765
"Hey," yourself.

07:34.833 --> 07:37.435
Where is everybody?

07:37.502 --> 07:38.702
Fi and Jesse
are doing a perimeter check,

07:38.770 --> 07:41.872
and Schmidt's making
our travel arrangements.

07:41.940 --> 07:43.674
I'm -- I'm actually trying to --
I'm helping you

07:43.742 --> 07:44.775
by calling you a douche bag!

07:44.843 --> 07:47.244
Yes, I am! Yes, I am.

07:47.312 --> 07:48.412
[ Gun clicks ]

07:48.480 --> 07:50.314
At least,
he's trying to.

07:50.382 --> 07:52.082
I didn't think
you'd be back.

07:52.150 --> 07:53.784
Well,
I wasn't sure myself.

07:53.852 --> 07:55.619
So, I went to see Elsa.

07:55.687 --> 07:58.589
Don't give me any crap
about breaking protocol.

07:58.657 --> 08:00.324
No, Sam, I'm glad that you did.
You should be 'cause she's the one

08:00.392 --> 08:02.293
who convinced me
to stick by you.

08:02.360 --> 08:04.829
She said if I abandoned
my best friend,

08:04.896 --> 08:07.398
then I'm not the guy
she fell in love with.

08:09.067 --> 08:11.902
I don't know what to say.
Thanks.

08:11.970 --> 08:14.638
Don't thank me 'cause I told her
we're not just running.

08:14.706 --> 08:16.207
As soon as we get
someplace safe,

08:16.274 --> 08:19.009
we're gonna sit down and figure
out a way to fix all of this.

08:19.077 --> 08:21.545
So, please, Mike,
don't make me a liar.

08:21.613 --> 08:23.247
I promise you
I'll make this right.

08:23.315 --> 08:27.384
I don't know how, but...
I will make this right, Sam.

08:27.452 --> 08:30.187
Oh, no. No, no.
We have a deal, Mr. Generous.

08:30.255 --> 08:34.758
And I hope that you die
in your sleep tonight!

08:34.826 --> 08:36.159
That didn't sound good.

08:38.330 --> 08:40.030
Getting you guys
out of the country

08:40.097 --> 08:43.100
is gonna be...more expensive
than we originally planned.

08:43.168 --> 08:44.201
How much?

08:44.269 --> 08:46.470
$200,000 a head.

08:46.538 --> 08:48.072
For fake I.D.s?!

08:48.139 --> 08:51.675
Not for fake I.D.s --
for fake <i>identities,</i> okay?

08:51.743 --> 08:54.979
And I'm talking work visas,
credit histories,

08:55.046 --> 08:56.647
and tax returns
going all the way back

08:56.715 --> 08:57.982
to the
Clinton administration.

08:58.049 --> 08:59.083
That's fantastic.

08:59.150 --> 09:00.751
It really is,
except for the part

09:00.819 --> 09:02.353
where it's gonna cost
800 grand.

09:02.420 --> 09:04.522
'Cause there's no way in hell
we can swing that.

09:04.589 --> 09:05.789
Fine, then I suggest
you build a raft

09:05.857 --> 09:07.191
and start
paddling to Cuba...

09:07.259 --> 09:09.193
Stop. Stop, stop.
...Because I have got nothing.

09:09.261 --> 09:11.896
Unless I throw the world's
most amazing bake sale

09:11.963 --> 09:14.398
in the next two --
Schmidt, stop talking!

09:14.466 --> 09:16.066
You still have
pricy merchandise

09:16.134 --> 09:17.835
sitting
in your warehouse, right?

09:17.903 --> 09:19.370
[ Sarcastically ]
Yes, in the warehouse!

09:19.437 --> 09:21.272
[ Fingers snap ] Problem solved.
Oh, wait a minute --

09:21.339 --> 09:24.408
you guys turned it into
a gigantic crime scene.

09:24.476 --> 09:26.677
There's cops all over the place.
You can't even get close.

09:26.745 --> 09:28.846
Let us worry about that.
[ Sighs ]

09:28.914 --> 09:32.016
What's the most expensive thing
that we can carry out?

09:32.083 --> 09:33.784
[ Scoffs ]
Well, all right.

09:33.852 --> 09:36.754
Assuming by some miracle
you get by the cops, okay,

09:36.821 --> 09:40.090
there is a compartment
where I keep certain items

09:40.158 --> 09:42.493
that I don't want my
stickier-fingered employees

09:42.561 --> 09:43.627
walking away with.

09:43.695 --> 09:44.929
Tell us
what we're looking for.

09:44.996 --> 09:47.531
You're looking for
a black case about yea big.

09:47.599 --> 09:52.102
I have a client who, upon
delivery, will pay $1 million.

09:52.170 --> 09:53.637
What's in the case?

09:53.705 --> 09:56.273
Call it
"sensitive electronics."

09:56.341 --> 09:58.475
Call your client.
Tell him to expect it tomorrow.

09:58.543 --> 10:01.545
Uh...Mike, I mean, every cop
south of the Mason-Dixon's

10:01.613 --> 10:02.846
looking for you,

10:02.914 --> 10:04.548
so you're not making a cameo
at a crime scene.

10:04.616 --> 10:06.116
And, honestly,
I shouldn't either.

10:06.184 --> 10:07.651
Half the force
knows this chin.

10:07.719 --> 10:08.852
I'll talk to Jesse and Fi.
[ Sighs ]

10:08.920 --> 10:10.454
They're gonna walk
into a suicide situation

10:10.522 --> 10:13.424
just because
you ask them to?

10:13.821 --> 10:14.955
Yeah, that's pretty much
how we roll.

10:15.023 --> 10:16.356
So, look, Schmidty,

10:16.424 --> 10:18.058
make sure you wear
something comfortable tomorrow

10:18.126 --> 10:19.660
'cause you're gonna
help them get it.

10:28.408 --> 10:33.378
Schmidt: Well, I'm no expert,
but I'm guessing a sealed door,

10:33.446 --> 10:37.218
plus three donut-eating cops,
equals a...go-home situation?

10:37.219 --> 10:39.186
Schmidt.
Let's go tell Michael we tried.

10:39.253 --> 10:41.721
Schmidt, can you hush for,
like, two seconds, please?

10:41.789 --> 10:44.190
Fi, check it out.

10:44.258 --> 10:46.593
[ Sighs ]
North wall -- 20 feet up.

10:46.660 --> 10:48.695
[ Gasps ]

10:48.762 --> 10:51.531
Thank you, Miami CSI,
for being out to lunch.

10:51.599 --> 10:53.499
I'm thinking we drive around
back, come up the alley on foot.

10:53.567 --> 10:56.035
Climb the truck,
squirrel through the window.

10:56.103 --> 10:58.671
[ Chuckling ] Wow, sorry, you --
you just said "squirrel"?

10:58.739 --> 11:00.940
Do I look like a guy
who "squirrels"?

11:01.008 --> 11:02.442
Do you really want us
to answer that?

11:02.509 --> 11:04.177
No, I don't.

11:04.245 --> 11:06.145
I was being rhetorical,
handsome.

11:08.215 --> 11:10.683
<i>Large security forces</i>
<i>can work to your advantage</i>

11:10.751 --> 11:13.353
<i>because each individual</i>
<i>thinks everybody else</i>

11:13.420 --> 11:15.021
<i>is paying attention.</i>

11:15.089 --> 11:17.757
<i>So, if you find a hole in</i>
<i>the security, you can get in.</i>

11:20.394 --> 11:22.328
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>if anything goes wrong,</i>

11:22.396 --> 11:25.899
<i>you're surrounded by the same</i>
<i>security forces you snuck past.</i>

11:25.966 --> 11:27.400
Jesse: Dude,
it's like two feet. Come on.

11:27.468 --> 11:28.902
Schmidt: Okay,
you gonna catch me?

11:28.969 --> 11:32.205
Yeah, I'll catch you.
Here we go. [ Grunts ] Okay.

11:32.273 --> 11:34.374
Great teamwork.
Thank you.

11:34.441 --> 11:36.442
Shh!
Just keep your voice down.

11:36.510 --> 11:38.745
Now, where the hell is this case?
Oh. [ Scoffs ]

11:38.812 --> 11:40.013
Follow me.

11:40.080 --> 11:42.916
And...I don't need
the tone, okay?

11:42.983 --> 11:44.050
[ Sighs ]

11:44.118 --> 11:46.986
Okay, okay, okay.
Hold up.

11:47.054 --> 11:54.127
Uh, go six...tiles,
four west, two...north.

11:54.194 --> 11:55.628
Shouldn't you have a parrot
on your shoulder?

11:55.696 --> 11:57.263
Oh. [ Scoffs ]
Hilarious.

11:57.331 --> 11:59.832
Okay.

11:59.900 --> 12:01.634
[ Grunting ] Look out.

12:03.938 --> 12:05.738
Have at it. I don't do
manual labor. [ Sighs ]

12:05.806 --> 12:07.907
Oh, I would never
have guessed.

12:07.975 --> 12:09.842
And this thing's
worth a fortune why, exactly?

12:09.910 --> 12:13.246
'Cause that is what someone
is willing to pay for it.

12:13.314 --> 12:14.614
[ Grunting ] Ah,
and it's heavy as hell.

12:14.682 --> 12:16.883
Lift with your knees.

12:16.951 --> 12:18.084
[ Grunts ]

12:21.121 --> 12:23.189
[ Grunting ] Aah, I think
I just slipped a disc.

12:23.257 --> 12:25.992
Hola, senoritas!
I missed you.

12:26.060 --> 12:27.560
What the hell are you doing?
What --

12:27.628 --> 12:29.195
[ bottle shatters ]
What the hell was that?

12:30.431 --> 12:31.864
You think somebody heard that?
Yes, they heard.

12:31.932 --> 12:33.666
No, no, no, no, no, no.
I -- I can't go to prison.

12:33.734 --> 12:35.668
I will not
do well in prison.

12:35.736 --> 12:36.636
Look, no one's
going to prison.

12:36.704 --> 12:38.404
[ Indistinct shouting ]

12:38.472 --> 12:40.373
We are gonna
bust our way out of here.

12:40.441 --> 12:42.508
[ Engine turns over ] Go through the wall
like the kool-aid guy?

12:42.576 --> 12:43.743
What are you, nuts?!

12:43.811 --> 12:45.345
Get in.

12:45.412 --> 12:47.113
Schmidt: Aah!

12:49.616 --> 12:53.453
Oh, God! Oh, God!

12:53.487 --> 12:55.722
Okay, drive.

12:55.789 --> 12:58.224
Watch the gates.
Oh!

12:58.292 --> 13:01.728
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa!
All right, go!

13:01.795 --> 13:03.629
Let's go.
Go, go, go, go, go!

13:08.002 --> 13:09.035
Jesse, you're driving.

13:31.492 --> 13:32.725
[ Bullets ricocheting ]

13:32.793 --> 13:33.860
[ Tires squeal ]

13:33.927 --> 13:36.095
Ooh! Drive,
bald man, drive!

13:41.902 --> 13:43.302
[ Engine shuts off ]

13:43.370 --> 13:44.570
[ Panting ] Okay.

13:44.638 --> 13:46.606
Okay.

13:46.673 --> 13:48.808
Is -- is anyone else
at 300 over 140?

13:48.876 --> 13:51.778
'Cause I -- I'm feeling
my heartbeat in my retinas.

13:51.845 --> 13:53.646
Everybody okay?
[ Scoffs ]

13:53.714 --> 13:54.847
Yeah, 'cause God
has a sense of humor.

13:54.915 --> 13:56.449
We should be shot!
We should be dead!

13:56.517 --> 13:58.818
Simmer down.
You're gonna blow a gasket.

13:58.886 --> 14:00.520
Fiona:
Oh, don't bother.

14:00.587 --> 14:01.721
He's been like this
the whole way here.

14:03.857 --> 14:06.059
Um...guys?

14:06.126 --> 14:09.462
Looks like the mystery box...
took a few bullets.

14:09.530 --> 14:10.830
Actually,
it took a lot of bullets.

14:10.898 --> 14:13.699
Well, good job,
super friends.

14:13.767 --> 14:15.835
It's destroyed. It's destroyed.
You got to be kidding me.

14:15.903 --> 14:19.205
Mike, this is bad.
This thing was our ticket out.

14:25.275 --> 14:26.642
Sam and Jesse
are picking up some new wheels

14:26.709 --> 14:27.643
in case we have to run.

14:27.710 --> 14:28.877
[ Door closes ]

14:28.945 --> 14:31.079
So, I'm just gonna
go ahead and ask --

14:31.147 --> 14:32.948
what the hell
is that thing?

14:33.016 --> 14:35.250
Schmidt: It <i>was</i>
<i>a remote circuit cutter.</i>

14:35.318 --> 14:37.219
It's for
disabling alarm systems.

14:37.287 --> 14:38.654
How does it work?

14:38.721 --> 14:41.556
How it <i>did</i> work --
it was -- okay, look.

14:41.624 --> 14:43.859
See -- see this?

14:43.926 --> 14:46.662
It's a collimator.
There's three of these.

14:46.729 --> 14:49.097
They fire gamma rays, same as
they use in brain surgery.

14:49.165 --> 14:50.799
And you aim these
at an alarm circuit

14:50.867 --> 14:53.835
and the point
where the beams cross...

14:53.903 --> 14:55.604
[ Clicks tongue ]
Kills all the electronics.

14:55.672 --> 14:57.239
[ Grunts ]
What am I gonna do?

14:57.307 --> 14:59.875
My -- my client
expects delivery on this!

14:59.942 --> 15:01.443
You're still
gonna deliver it.

15:01.511 --> 15:04.780
[ Laughing ] No, I'm not,
as it is broken.

15:04.847 --> 15:06.648
And unless one of you
has a degree in quantum physics,

15:06.716 --> 15:09.418
there's no way to fix it.
We don't have to fix it.

15:09.485 --> 15:11.720
We just need to make it look
good enough for the hand-off.

15:11.788 --> 15:14.189
Call your client,
buy as much time as you can.

15:14.257 --> 15:17.426
No, my -- my client robs
and kills people for a living.

15:17.493 --> 15:20.062
So, we don't have to feel bad
about ripping him off.

15:20.129 --> 15:22.331
[ Stammers ]

15:22.398 --> 15:24.232
Just for the record,
I think this is a terrible idea,

15:24.300 --> 15:27.602
and I think that you are not
in a rational head space.

15:27.670 --> 15:28.770
Hey!

15:28.838 --> 15:31.773
Yep.
[ Chuckling ] It's me.

15:31.841 --> 15:33.075
Um...Okay.

15:33.142 --> 15:36.211
Well, listen, I-I --
I-I hit some delays.

15:36.279 --> 15:42.951
Uh...I can have this thing
for you next Tuesday, easily.

15:43.019 --> 15:46.755
Okay. Oh, okay.
[ Laughing ] All right.

15:46.823 --> 15:48.156
Okay, bye.

15:48.224 --> 15:50.826
He says if he doesn't have this
by 4:00 today,

15:50.893 --> 15:52.728
he will shoot me
in the throat.

15:52.795 --> 15:55.163
Well, that doesn't give us
much time to fake this thing.

15:55.231 --> 15:56.231
Well, then,
we better get started.

15:56.299 --> 15:57.099
[ Metal clatters ]
Mm!

16:02.505 --> 16:06.041
<i>As a spy, you deal with</i>
<i>a lot of dangerous people</i>

16:06.109 --> 16:07.909
<i>and a lot</i>
<i>of dangerous technology.</i>

16:07.977 --> 16:10.212
<i>Since it's a bad idea</i>
<i>to put them together,</i>

16:10.279 --> 16:14.816
<i>you get pretty good at</i>
<i>faking sophisticated hardware.</i>

16:14.884 --> 16:18.286
<i>The good news is that the more</i>
<i>high-end the technology,</i>

16:18.354 --> 16:21.356
<i>the less likely your buyer is</i>
<i>to know how it works.</i>

16:21.424 --> 16:23.558
<i>Hand them a device</i>
<i>that looks right, feels right,</i>

16:23.626 --> 16:25.994
<i>and sounds right,</i>
<i>and it should do the trick.</i>

16:26.062 --> 16:27.662
[ Whirring ]

16:27.730 --> 16:29.264
[ Whirring stops ]

16:29.332 --> 16:31.733
<i>And adding a listening device</i>
<i>is never a bad idea.</i>

16:33.569 --> 16:35.604
Oh, one more thing --
for luck.

16:35.671 --> 16:38.206
Fi, we already have ears
on the meeting.

16:38.274 --> 16:40.709
The last thing we want
is a gun in Schmidt's hands.

16:40.777 --> 16:42.744
Well, what if something happens
and we don't get there in time?

16:42.812 --> 16:45.013
Fi, we have a plan.

16:45.081 --> 16:46.415
Don't take this personally,

16:46.482 --> 16:49.184
but our plans haven't been
going so well lately.

16:53.623 --> 16:56.691
<i>When you have a full-time</i>
<i>surveillance team on your tail,</i>

16:56.759 --> 16:58.560
<i>it's difficult</i>
<i>to set private meetings.</i>

16:58.628 --> 17:01.630
<i>So, if you need</i>
<i>to arrange a sit-down</i>

17:01.697 --> 17:03.832
<i>with someone</i>
<i>you can't contact directly,</i>

17:03.900 --> 17:05.834
<i>you have to</i>
<i>contact them indirectly.</i>

17:05.902 --> 17:07.969
Barry Burkowski --
I have an appointment.

17:08.037 --> 17:10.338
B-u-r-k...owski.

17:10.406 --> 17:14.142
Burkowski --
no, I don't see you.

17:14.210 --> 17:15.577
What are you
talking about?

17:15.645 --> 17:17.078
I got a call from a nurse
that said I needed to come down

17:17.146 --> 17:18.512
right away
for some tests.

17:18.580 --> 17:21.282
Some tests regarding a,
um...

17:21.349 --> 17:22.517
[ Clicks tongue ]

17:22.585 --> 17:25.820
Aggressive fungus --
in a very sensitive area.

17:25.887 --> 17:27.189
I'm sorry.

17:27.256 --> 17:29.191
We don't have an appointment
for a Barry Burkowski.

17:29.258 --> 17:30.625
Really?

17:30.693 --> 17:32.127
Well, that's too bad for you
because I'm not going anywhere

17:32.195 --> 17:34.262
until I see a doctor and they
tell me that I'm parasite-free.

17:34.330 --> 17:38.033
So, you work it out.

17:38.100 --> 17:41.736
Barry.
Funny running into you.

17:41.804 --> 17:43.705
Mrs. Westen.
What are the odds of --

17:43.773 --> 17:46.274
It was you.

17:46.342 --> 17:47.809
You set
this appointment.

17:47.877 --> 17:49.711
Well, the good news is
you don't have a fungus.

17:49.779 --> 17:54.149
The bad news is...
Michael needs your help.

17:54.217 --> 17:56.551
You mean your fugitive son,
"he who must not be named"?

17:56.619 --> 17:57.919
Yes, him.

17:57.987 --> 18:00.021
Wait a minute,
aren't you supposed to have,

18:00.089 --> 18:02.090
like, a team of 24/7
federal babysitters?

18:02.158 --> 18:03.525
Actually, I do.
[ Chuckles ]

18:03.593 --> 18:05.594
In fact, they were nice enough
to drop me off.

18:05.661 --> 18:06.828
Okay,
hold on a second.

18:06.896 --> 18:08.430
I think my brain
just exploded.

18:08.498 --> 18:09.831
What if
they see us talking?

18:09.899 --> 18:11.366
Don't worry.

18:11.434 --> 18:12.334
They're waiting for me in
a coffee shop down the street.

18:12.401 --> 18:14.769
Now, unless you want me

18:14.837 --> 18:17.138
to introduce them
to you personally,

18:17.206 --> 18:19.975
I would suggest
that you hear me out.

18:20.042 --> 18:23.311
Yeah, but, uh...
Let's just do this somewhere

18:23.379 --> 18:24.746
a little more private.

18:24.814 --> 18:27.549
Perfect.
Um...Okay.

18:27.617 --> 18:28.850
Let me
get this straight now.

18:28.918 --> 18:32.020
Mike wants me to throw up
a financial smoke screen

18:32.088 --> 18:34.656
for every agency
in the known universe?

18:34.724 --> 18:37.192
Well, you usually hide money
to avoid the authorities,

18:37.260 --> 18:38.693
so now just...
do the opposite.

18:38.761 --> 18:40.562
"Do the opposite."

18:40.630 --> 18:42.931
There could be
some serious blowback here.

18:42.999 --> 18:44.432
You know, that never stopped
Michael from helping <i>you.</i>

18:44.500 --> 18:45.867
How many times
has he saved your ass?

18:45.935 --> 18:47.769
Three, four times?

18:47.837 --> 18:49.504
I have saved his,
too.

18:50.773 --> 18:52.140
All right, well,
I've <i>helped</i> save.

18:52.208 --> 18:53.808
[ Inhales deeply ]

18:53.876 --> 18:55.443
Fine, look,
I'm gonna do it.

18:55.511 --> 18:57.178
Good -- 'cause it needs
to be done today.

18:57.246 --> 18:58.680
All right.

18:58.748 --> 19:01.349
Now...I need you to bring the
account numbers to this address.

19:01.417 --> 19:02.751
[ Paper rips ]

19:02.818 --> 19:05.387
This is my loft
in the design district.

19:05.454 --> 19:07.455
Be careful.
Make sure you're not followed.

19:07.523 --> 19:08.690
All right,
thanks, Barry.

19:08.758 --> 19:10.091
Oh, and, Mrs. Westen,
one thing --

19:10.159 --> 19:11.826
the next time
that you set up a meeting

19:11.894 --> 19:13.428
with somebody
in a doctor's office,

19:13.496 --> 19:15.463
just go with something easy
like...gluten allergy.

19:15.531 --> 19:17.966
'Cause the fungus
down under...

19:18.034 --> 19:20.435
[ Inhales deeply ]
...freaked me out.

19:20.503 --> 19:23.471
Good to know.
Thanks.

19:26.108 --> 19:27.175
I can't do this,
all right?

19:27.243 --> 19:28.710
Yes, you can. See?

19:28.778 --> 19:30.679
The gizmo looks as good as new.
This'll be a cakewalk.

19:30.746 --> 19:32.180
Yeah, that's easy
for you to say.

19:32.248 --> 19:34.482
You don't have to stare
into the abyss of Thorne's eyes

19:34.550 --> 19:35.650
and try to rip him off.

19:35.718 --> 19:37.719
Take a breath.
[ Breathes deeply ]

19:37.787 --> 19:40.288
Good, now describe
how a meeting usually goes.

19:40.356 --> 19:42.591
So, I show up.
Uh...I say hi.

19:42.658 --> 19:45.560
Sometimes he says hi --
not usually.

19:45.628 --> 19:47.429
And then I give him
the merchandise.

19:47.496 --> 19:48.730
He gives me the cash.

19:48.798 --> 19:50.198
And you
go your separate ways.

19:50.266 --> 19:53.368
Yes. B-but what if he asks me
to demonstrate how this works?

19:53.436 --> 19:54.736
Has he ever
asked that before?

19:54.804 --> 19:56.371
No, but he --
then don't explain anything.

19:56.439 --> 19:57.739
[ Sighs ]

19:57.807 --> 20:00.175
Just give him the case,
take the money, walk away.

20:00.242 --> 20:01.610
Like it's any other deal.

20:01.677 --> 20:03.645
But this not any other deal,
is it?

20:03.713 --> 20:05.046
B-because
in any other deal,

20:05.114 --> 20:07.515
I'm not selling him
a broken box for $1 million.

20:07.583 --> 20:08.950
W-where's the gun
in this?

20:09.018 --> 20:10.085
Fiona said
she put a gun in here.

20:10.152 --> 20:12.287
How does it come out?
Hold on.

20:12.355 --> 20:13.888
There's a gun
underneath that panel,

20:13.956 --> 20:15.523
but don't even think
about going for it.

20:15.591 --> 20:16.958
'Cause the chances
of you blowing off your big toe

20:17.026 --> 20:18.760
are much better
than hitting Thorne.

20:18.828 --> 20:20.662
Now, we got to go.

20:20.730 --> 20:24.833
Schmidt, when in doubt,
keep your mouth shut.

20:24.900 --> 20:26.701
Okay.

20:33.776 --> 20:38.179
Uh...I assume
the Mike in this is working

20:38.247 --> 20:39.881
and you guys
can all hear me.

20:39.949 --> 20:41.182
Uh, if I die today,

20:41.250 --> 20:44.352
my ghost will haunt
your children's children.

20:44.420 --> 20:46.554
It'll be like one of those
Japanese movie ghosts, too --

20:46.622 --> 20:48.857
like the little girl
floating.

20:48.924 --> 20:49.958
Really creepy.

20:50.026 --> 20:51.393
[ Sighs ]

20:51.460 --> 20:52.727
Michael, are you sure
he's gonna be able to sell this?

20:52.795 --> 20:55.263
Jesse: Seriously, Mike,
dude looks like a hot mess.

20:55.331 --> 20:57.532
Michael: He'll sell it.
He has no choice.

20:59.568 --> 21:03.471
Get ready --
I think our buyer's here.

21:07.810 --> 21:09.277
[ Chuckling ] Thorne.

21:09.345 --> 21:12.947
You look well...armed.
[ Chuckles ]

21:13.015 --> 21:14.215
What can I say?
I always come prepared.

21:14.283 --> 21:16.384
I missed you,
little buddy.

21:16.452 --> 21:18.720
If I didn't know better,
I'd swear you were ducking me.

21:18.788 --> 21:19.921
[ Scoffs ]

21:19.989 --> 21:21.089
Why would I duck
my favorite client?

21:23.993 --> 21:25.360
Where the hell you been?

21:25.428 --> 21:26.828
Oh, you know,
doing my thing.

21:26.896 --> 21:30.231
Uh...there was a whole backup
with my warehouse --

21:30.299 --> 21:32.534
Yeah, whatever.

21:32.601 --> 21:34.235
I didn't ask you for your life story.
Are we gonna do this, or what?

21:34.303 --> 21:37.238
Yes. Uh, I believe
this is yours.

21:37.306 --> 21:38.807
Okay.

21:40.810 --> 21:41.676
[ Sighs ]

21:46.916 --> 21:48.917
My, oh, my.
She is a thing of beauty.

21:48.984 --> 21:50.051
[ Chuckling ] Yeah.

21:50.119 --> 21:52.754
[ Tinking ]

21:52.822 --> 21:54.355
Hey.

21:54.423 --> 21:55.757
What the hell's up
with this?

21:55.825 --> 21:57.392
What...the hell's...
up with what?

21:57.460 --> 21:58.927
The specs I gave you said
that the housing

21:58.994 --> 21:59.928
was supposed to be
platinum.

21:59.995 --> 22:01.396
Wait, what?

22:01.464 --> 22:02.564
<i>In almost any operation,</i>

22:02.631 --> 22:03.998
<i>there's a moment</i>
<i>when everything</i>

22:04.066 --> 22:05.600
<i>hangs in the balance,</i>

22:05.668 --> 22:07.902
<i>when a dribble of sweat,</i>
<i>a clumsy answer,</i>

22:07.970 --> 22:10.271
<i>or even a stutter</i>
<i>could get you killed.</i>

22:10.339 --> 22:12.073
Why didn't I use platinum?
Yes.

22:12.141 --> 22:13.842
Because, look,
this is tungsten.

22:13.909 --> 22:17.479
Okay, th-this keeps
the gamma rays from leaking

22:17.546 --> 22:19.047
better than platinum.

22:19.115 --> 22:20.515
Tungsten's
all the rage now.

22:20.583 --> 22:21.816
Is that so?

22:21.884 --> 22:24.552
Yes, that's so.

22:24.620 --> 22:26.187
Michael:
Damn it, walk away.

22:26.255 --> 22:27.989
I told him
to walk away.

22:28.057 --> 22:30.558
Take the money
and walk away, Schmidt.

22:30.626 --> 22:33.027
In fact, my tech said so,
who, by the way,

22:33.095 --> 22:36.064
completely upgraded
the calibration

22:36.132 --> 22:38.333
and guidance systems
free of charge.

22:38.400 --> 22:40.101
And, y-you know,
that's why you come to me.

22:40.169 --> 22:42.771
I go the extra mile --
[ Grunts ]

22:42.838 --> 22:44.339
You showed this to a tech?
What tech?

22:44.406 --> 22:45.974
He's cool! He's cool, okay?
He's a Professor.

22:46.041 --> 22:47.375
He does this kind of stuff
all the time.

22:47.443 --> 22:48.676
[ Chuckling ]
It's not a big deal.

22:48.744 --> 22:51.012
It's a huge deal because
it's not what I asked for!

22:51.080 --> 22:52.413
Sorry.

22:52.481 --> 22:54.315
Schmidty, if this
has a bunch of changes,

22:54.383 --> 22:56.651
I don't know if I'm still
gonna be able to use it.

22:56.719 --> 22:58.553
That's why he said
he is coming here

22:58.621 --> 23:00.421
to walk you through
the whole thing.

23:00.489 --> 23:01.790
He's on his way
right now.

23:03.259 --> 23:04.826
Did he just say his tech
is on his way?

23:04.894 --> 23:06.261
What the hell
is he talking about?

23:06.328 --> 23:07.362
We got to go in.

23:07.429 --> 23:08.997
No, no. Hold off.
Hold off.

23:09.064 --> 23:11.533
If they're waiting on a tech,
let's just give them one.

23:11.600 --> 23:13.201
Everybody
watch my back.

23:13.269 --> 23:14.869
No, Sam, you're not going in there.
You don't know how it works.

23:14.937 --> 23:16.304
No, Schmidt gave me
the whole spiel on how it works.

23:16.372 --> 23:17.539
I'll be fine.

23:17.606 --> 23:19.240
I'm not putting you
in that position, Sam.

23:19.308 --> 23:23.511
Well, you're not -- I am.
I got this.

23:23.579 --> 23:25.246
Good luck.
Thanks, brother.

23:31.921 --> 23:34.289
I don't see this tech.

23:34.356 --> 23:35.657
He's coming.

23:35.724 --> 23:36.825
He's coming.
When, Christmas?

23:36.892 --> 23:38.526
[ Grunts ]
I don't like this.

23:38.594 --> 23:39.761
I don't like this
at all.

23:43.899 --> 23:46.301
I say we take him
out to the Everglades

23:46.368 --> 23:47.769
and find us an alligator. Grab him.
Okay, listen --

23:47.837 --> 23:49.838
wait! He --
afternoon, gentlemen.

23:49.905 --> 23:51.472
Oh, there he is.
Hey. Hey!

23:51.540 --> 23:53.074
Hey, guy.
Glad you made it.

23:53.142 --> 23:54.375
Yeah, so am I.

23:54.443 --> 23:55.977
Hey, geniuses,
thanks for setting up a meeting

23:56.045 --> 23:57.412
in the middle
of rush hour.

23:57.479 --> 23:58.980
Settle down.
What's your name?

23:59.048 --> 24:00.215
Dr. Charles Finley.

24:00.282 --> 24:02.250
Schmidt said you
wanted to review my work.

24:02.318 --> 24:04.452
Most of the upgrades, frankly,
are gonna go...

24:04.520 --> 24:08.089
way over your head,
but the operation is the same.

24:08.157 --> 24:09.991
Guidance and calibration
have been revamped.

24:10.059 --> 24:11.993
Most importantly, though,
the collimator velocity --

24:12.061 --> 24:12.961
that's the story
of the day.

24:13.028 --> 24:14.395
Okay, save it, Einstein.

24:14.463 --> 24:17.298
We were planning a little
dry run with the cutter anyway.

24:17.366 --> 24:18.466
You're coming with.

24:18.534 --> 24:19.400
Oh, well,
that's not possible.

24:19.468 --> 24:20.702
[ Sighs ]

24:20.769 --> 24:22.036
See, I'm just here
to show you how this works.

24:22.104 --> 24:23.137
I've got important research
to get back --

24:23.205 --> 24:24.439
[ gun cocks ]

24:24.506 --> 24:26.441
Your beakers will be there
when you get back, Doc.

24:26.508 --> 24:28.009
Let's go.

24:32.401 --> 24:34.039
This is crazy.
Just listen to me.

24:34.111 --> 24:35.311
You want to
test the cutter?

24:35.379 --> 24:36.379
That's fine.
We'll book some time at my lab.

24:36.447 --> 24:37.647
We'll do it
the right way.

24:37.715 --> 24:40.717
We can do it your way
when you make the rules.

24:40.784 --> 24:42.485
Today's my day.
Get in the truck.

24:42.553 --> 24:44.020
Well, we need to know
where we're going first.

24:44.088 --> 24:45.188
Never mind that --
you'll find out.

24:45.256 --> 24:46.723
No, no!
Not "never mind."

24:46.790 --> 24:48.124
Not even close.

24:48.192 --> 24:49.459
Look, if I'm breaking into
some nuclear facility,

24:49.526 --> 24:50.593
I've got to know.

24:50.661 --> 24:53.963
[ Sighing ] Okay.

24:54.031 --> 24:55.431
The place
is called Pharmatech.

24:55.499 --> 24:57.634
It's in Fort Lauderdale.
They're closed on the weekends.

24:57.701 --> 25:01.738
As long as the toy works on
the back door, you'll be fine.

25:04.341 --> 25:06.042
In case you forgot,
this thing doesn't work.

25:06.110 --> 25:08.711
They're going to kill .
Just stay calm, okay?

25:08.779 --> 25:11.481
My friends are listening in --
they'll help us out.

25:11.548 --> 25:13.182
[ Sighs ]
So, what now?

25:13.250 --> 25:14.083
We get to Pharmatech
and set something up

25:14.151 --> 25:15.451
before they get there.

25:15.519 --> 25:17.820
That's off A1A --
it's got to be 45 minutes away.

25:17.888 --> 25:19.422
I'll have us there
in 30.

25:19.490 --> 25:20.523
[ Engine turns over ]

25:23.727 --> 25:28.598
<i>Banking security algorithms</i>
<i>look for anything unusual --</i>

25:28.666 --> 25:30.733
<i>transfers in large amounts,</i>
<i>on the same day,</i>

25:30.801 --> 25:33.403
<i>or to multiple countries</i>
<i>at the same time.</i>

25:33.470 --> 25:35.972
<i>Do any one of those,</i>
<i>and you might get red-flagged.</i>

25:36.040 --> 25:38.608
<i>Do all of them, and you'll send</i>
<i>the authorities looking for you</i>

25:38.676 --> 25:40.109
<i>anywhere you want them to.</i>

25:40.177 --> 25:43.079
One more transfer to the bank
in Moldova, and we're done.

25:43.147 --> 25:44.380
CIA and Interpol --
they're gonna be

25:44.448 --> 25:46.049
chasing their tails
hunting for Mike like a --

25:46.116 --> 25:48.384
[ telephone rings, beeps ]

25:48.452 --> 25:50.019
Yo. What?

25:50.087 --> 25:52.655
Whoa, come again?

25:52.723 --> 25:55.224
Where are they now?
Okay. Thanks for the tip.

25:55.292 --> 25:56.893
[ Telephone beeps ]
What was that?

25:56.961 --> 25:58.428
My little bird at the Miami P.D.
just informed me

25:58.495 --> 26:00.496
that there's a federal raid
scheduled for here

26:00.564 --> 26:02.532
in 10 minutes.

26:02.599 --> 26:04.133
I thought you told me
these transfers

26:04.201 --> 26:05.535
couldn't be traced
back to you!

26:05.602 --> 26:07.537
They can't!
They must have followed you.

26:07.604 --> 26:09.672
No way in hell,
Barry!

26:09.740 --> 26:11.841
Did you phone anyone?
Anyone at all?!

26:11.909 --> 26:14.277
No...one important.

26:14.345 --> 26:16.379
No, I had to cancel
a tanning session

26:16.447 --> 26:18.915
and an O2 session --
that's it.

26:18.983 --> 26:20.383
You're a known associate
of Michael Westen's.

26:20.451 --> 26:22.819
All of these cancellations is
probably what tipped them off.

26:22.886 --> 26:24.187
Yeah, well, you know,

26:24.254 --> 26:26.622
sue me for not wanting
to screw over my manscapist.

26:26.690 --> 26:28.358
You know, hanging out
with your family

26:28.425 --> 26:29.559
is like having
a venereal disease --

26:29.626 --> 26:31.494
it's the gift
that just keeps on giving.

26:31.562 --> 26:32.339
You're right. It's my fault.

26:32.364 --> 26:33.396
I should probably never have
brought these here.

26:33.397 --> 26:35.031
Look, technically,
it's Mike's fault, okay?

26:35.099 --> 26:36.899
But we can
do this blame game later.

26:36.967 --> 26:40.036
There is a fire escape
off the east sun porch, so go.

26:40.104 --> 26:41.437
Aren't you coming?
No!

26:41.505 --> 26:43.072
These hard drives are not
gonna slag themselves.

26:43.140 --> 26:44.674
Plus, I've got my ledger,
my files --

26:44.742 --> 26:45.842
I'm not
leaving you behind!

26:45.909 --> 26:47.443
Yes, you are, Mrs. Westen.
Now go.

26:47.511 --> 26:49.612
Seriously, there's no point
in <i>both</i> of us getting caught!

26:49.680 --> 26:52.715
Get out of here!
Go! Scram!

26:52.783 --> 26:54.884
I-I'm sorry, Barry.

26:54.952 --> 26:57.453
Tell Mike he owes me --
again!

26:57.521 --> 26:59.589
[ Electricity hums ]

27:09.166 --> 27:10.967
[ Cellphone ringing ]

27:14.238 --> 27:17.407
[ Cellphone beeps ]
Hello.

27:17.474 --> 27:18.775
Mrs. Westen,
in the last 10 minutes

27:18.842 --> 27:20.410
I've received calls
from Scotland Yard, Interpol,

27:20.477 --> 27:22.645
and some jackass
in the Moldovan army.

27:22.713 --> 27:24.680
They're all
deploying assault teams

27:24.748 --> 27:27.216
based on new leads
on your son's whereabouts.

27:27.284 --> 27:30.186
The thing is, each lead is in
a different corner of the globe.

27:30.254 --> 27:31.554
Sounds like you've got
a lot of important,

27:31.622 --> 27:32.755
pissed-off people
on your hands.

27:32.823 --> 27:34.791
Why are you calling me?

27:34.858 --> 27:37.393
Because you put Burkowski
up to this.

27:37.461 --> 27:38.761
Really?
What makes you say that?

27:38.829 --> 27:40.830
I found three cigarette butts
in his ash tray.

27:40.898 --> 27:42.732
They happen to be
your favorite brand.

27:42.800 --> 27:44.467
And once the DNA work
comes back,

27:44.535 --> 27:46.569
I'll have proof
that you were involved.

27:46.637 --> 27:49.605
You've crossed the rubicon,
Mrs. Westen, and now I -- [ Click ]

27:52.709 --> 27:54.177
[ Sighs ]

28:02.352 --> 28:06.355
Looks like
we beat them here.

28:06.423 --> 28:08.558
Okay. Thorne said they're gonna be
doing the test on the back door.

28:08.625 --> 28:09.725
How do you
want to play it?

28:09.793 --> 28:10.993
If they're following
the speed limits,

28:11.061 --> 28:12.361
we've got about 10 minutes
before they get here.

28:12.429 --> 28:14.230
I say we shoot this out.

28:14.298 --> 28:16.299
Fi, these guys have machine
guns. Sam would get killed.

28:16.366 --> 28:18.367
Well, Sam will be killed for sure
when that circuit cutter doesn't work.

28:18.435 --> 28:20.303
She's right, Mike. There's no way
of turning off the alarms from the inside.

28:20.370 --> 28:22.338
Then we'll do it
from the inside.

28:22.406 --> 28:24.307
Do you think
the two security guards

28:24.374 --> 28:25.675
might have something to say
about that?

28:25.742 --> 28:28.377
I guess
we'll find out.

28:28.445 --> 28:32.048
<i>Spies love buildings</i>
<i>with assigned parking spaces.</i>

28:32.116 --> 28:34.183
<i>If you need to</i>
<i>talk your way past security,</i>

28:34.251 --> 28:37.220
<i>they give you the name</i>
<i>of the company's employees,</i>

28:37.287 --> 28:40.189
<i>their positions,</i>
<i>and even how powerful they are,</i>

28:40.257 --> 28:42.992
<i>all with just a stroll</i>
<i>through the parking lot.</i>

28:43.060 --> 28:44.961
Hello!

28:45.028 --> 28:46.996
Building's closed
on Saturdays.

28:47.064 --> 28:49.599
Yeah, I know.
We actually work here.

28:49.666 --> 28:52.034
I'm Don Sterling
on the third floor.

28:52.102 --> 28:53.503
I lost my wallet,

28:53.570 --> 28:55.438
and Roger here
demagnetized his key.

28:55.506 --> 28:57.773
Cellphone.
I'm sorry. I can't let you guys in.

28:57.841 --> 28:58.908
We understand
you got a job to do.

28:58.976 --> 29:00.343
We totally
respect that --

29:00.410 --> 29:03.646
we have this huge presentation
for an FDA bigwig on Monday.

29:03.714 --> 29:05.414
We're a little
behind the eight ball.

29:05.482 --> 29:07.283
Look, I wish
I could help you guys out.

29:07.351 --> 29:08.651
If you want to
talk to my supervisor,

29:08.719 --> 29:10.286
I could give you his number.

29:10.354 --> 29:12.188
I get it --
I totally understand.

29:12.256 --> 29:14.290
You are such an idiot!
Don, this is all your fault.

29:14.358 --> 29:15.892
I'm an idiot? My fault?
If you hadn't been drinking your lunch

29:15.959 --> 29:17.193
out of a Martini glass
all week,

29:17.261 --> 29:18.528
we wouldn't be
in this mess in the first place.

29:18.595 --> 29:20.696
That's rich coming from
"Roger Dodger,"

29:20.764 --> 29:22.798
who's been dead weight
since day one!

29:22.866 --> 29:24.100
What'd you call me?
"Dead weight"!

29:24.168 --> 29:25.701
Dead weight?
I'm dead weight?

29:25.769 --> 29:28.571
I'm dead weight?
Dead weight, day one!

29:28.639 --> 29:31.374
Hey, break it up!
Hey! Break it up!

29:31.441 --> 29:32.775
Break it up!
Break it up!

29:35.979 --> 29:38.748
Look, we're not
gonna hurt you,

29:38.815 --> 29:41.417
but we need you to take us
to the control room now.

29:41.485 --> 29:43.819
Find it yourself.
Seriously.

29:43.887 --> 29:45.655
[ Sighs ] They're here.
[ Sighs ]

29:45.722 --> 29:47.223
We need to turn off
those alarms now.

29:47.291 --> 29:48.658
Jesse: Okay.

29:48.725 --> 29:51.928
Frick and Frack are gonna make
us do this the hard way.

29:51.995 --> 29:55.131
The schematics
to their security system.

29:55.199 --> 29:57.733
Now, the main chip
to the keypad is here,

29:57.801 --> 30:00.002
six inches back from the wall.
You think you can handle that?

30:00.070 --> 30:01.871
Does a black hole suck?

30:01.939 --> 30:05.875
Okay, Professor, show me
what that bad boy can do.

30:05.943 --> 30:07.443
Is there a whiff
of a plan here,

30:07.511 --> 30:09.712
or is this like a wait-and-die
kind of situation?

30:09.780 --> 30:11.981
Just keep it together.
I saw Fi's car on the way in.

30:12.049 --> 30:14.050
We just got to buy them time
to figure something out.

30:20.791 --> 30:22.291
Grab the keys.

30:25.529 --> 30:27.230
Thorne:
See that light there?

30:27.297 --> 30:28.264
That means
the alarm is armed.

30:28.332 --> 30:30.499
Turn it off.
No problemo.

30:30.567 --> 30:33.970
Just realize it takes about a
minute and a half to calibrate.

30:34.037 --> 30:36.105
Yeah, whatever. Just hurry up --
we can't stand here all day.

30:36.173 --> 30:37.773
And we can't rush this,
either.

30:37.841 --> 30:40.009
It's not like I'm programming
a coffee maker.

30:40.077 --> 30:42.111
So, please stand by.
Schematics, please?

30:42.179 --> 30:45.248
Fiona: Come on, guys.
Please, tell me which key it is.

30:45.315 --> 30:48.050
We're trying to save a man's
life here -- two, if it matters.

30:48.118 --> 30:50.019
Go to hell.
[ Sighs ]

30:50.087 --> 30:51.354
Look, I get it --
you hate us.

30:51.421 --> 30:54.323
More to the left.

30:54.391 --> 30:56.525
[ Beeping ]

30:56.593 --> 30:58.227
And...Ah! Too far.

30:58.295 --> 30:59.328
Thorne:
You know what I think?

30:59.396 --> 31:01.797
I think you're
trying to rip me off

31:01.865 --> 31:03.432
by selling me
this piece of crap.

31:03.500 --> 31:05.568
Do you know that every time you
distract me, you slow me down?

31:05.636 --> 31:07.036
Do you realize that?

31:07.104 --> 31:08.838
So, let me just do my work,
please.

31:11.041 --> 31:13.142
Move!

31:15.712 --> 31:16.612
[ Gun cocks ]

31:16.680 --> 31:18.547
Time's up, Professor.

31:18.615 --> 31:21.584
I said do it -- now.

31:21.652 --> 31:22.518
[ Beep ]

31:25.155 --> 31:26.255
There we go.

31:26.323 --> 31:28.357
Turned it off --
just like I said.

31:28.425 --> 31:31.560
Hmm.

31:35.232 --> 31:37.133
[ Beep ]
[ Sighs ]

31:37.200 --> 31:39.335
That was un-fun.

31:39.403 --> 31:41.203
[ Car door opens, closes ]

31:41.271 --> 31:44.874
[ Chuckling ] Well, Thorne,
it has been fun.

31:44.941 --> 31:47.243
But we're
gonna wrap it up.

31:47.311 --> 31:50.112
Thorne: Yeah, we're not
wrapping anything up just yet.

31:50.180 --> 31:52.315
I mean, your buddy here
did such a bang-up job,

31:52.382 --> 31:53.916
I'm gonna
need him tomorrow, too.

31:53.984 --> 31:55.785
You want him
on the heist?!

31:55.852 --> 31:57.953
What are you, high?
That's not part of the deal.

31:58.021 --> 32:00.456
Schmidt, buddy, I thought
you went the extra mile

32:00.524 --> 32:01.957
for your clients?

32:02.025 --> 32:05.695
I'll tell you what -- I'll throw
in an extra $100k as a bonus.

32:05.762 --> 32:07.530
Uh, look.
Thanks, but no thanks.

32:07.597 --> 32:09.932
Come on, I'm a scientist,
not a master thief.

32:10.000 --> 32:11.734
So, if you can
just take us home.

32:11.802 --> 32:14.670
You go home
after you do the job,

32:14.738 --> 32:17.440
or you don't go home at all,
Professor.

32:17.507 --> 32:18.341
[ Car door closes ]
Let's go.

32:18.408 --> 32:19.809
[ Engine turns over ]

32:22.019 --> 32:24.766
<i>Like terrorists,</i>
<i>organized criminals,</i>

32:24.767 --> 32:26.702
<i>tend to be cautious</i>
<i>about the people they work with</i>

32:26.769 --> 32:29.037
<i>right before a major operation.</i>

32:29.105 --> 32:30.739
<i>They watch you when you eat,</i>

32:30.807 --> 32:33.542
<i>post someone outside the door</i>
<i>when you go to the bathroom,</i>

32:33.610 --> 32:36.245
<i>and force you</i>
<i>to sleep under lock and key.</i>

32:36.312 --> 32:38.413
<i>That is,</i>
<i>assuming you can sleep.</i>

32:38.481 --> 32:41.116
Sam. Hey, Sam!

32:41.184 --> 32:44.086
Jesus. What the hell
are you doing?

32:44.154 --> 32:45.420
Look, every time
I close my eyes,

32:45.488 --> 32:48.223
I-I see bullets flying
and blood and entrails and --

32:48.291 --> 32:49.625
Okay, just stop.

32:49.692 --> 32:51.660
I don't know how you can
just lie there, slumbering away,

32:51.728 --> 32:54.129
knowing that tomorrow
we're helping a psychopath

32:54.197 --> 32:57.499
with a heist with a piece
of equipment that does not work.

32:57.567 --> 33:00.869
Okay, look, the bug in the
cutter doohickey is still on,

33:00.937 --> 33:02.504
so once Mike hears
what those jokers are up to,

33:02.572 --> 33:04.306
he'll come back
and save us.

33:04.374 --> 33:06.008
Yeah, 'cause everything
he's touched has come up aces.

33:06.075 --> 33:08.310
You watch it.
Shut up and go to sleep.

33:08.378 --> 33:09.845
The last thing we need
is to be stumbling around

33:09.913 --> 33:11.413
like a couple
of zombies tomorrow.

33:14.083 --> 33:15.117
[ Sighs ]

33:15.185 --> 33:16.919
Do you mind
if we trade cots?

33:16.986 --> 33:18.120
Go to sleep, Schmidt.

33:19.756 --> 33:21.523
Thorne:
Up and at them, ladies.

33:21.591 --> 33:22.824
[ Sighs ]
Game time.

33:24.260 --> 33:25.661
[ Grunts ]

33:25.728 --> 33:27.095
[ Imitates explosion ]

33:27.163 --> 33:29.064
All right, listen up.
I just heard from my guy.

33:29.132 --> 33:31.867
Turns out the trade show
is much bigger than we thought.

33:31.935 --> 33:35.404
The Miami Gem Center
is holding -- and wait for it --

33:35.471 --> 33:40.876
$90 million worth of stones
in their vaults.

33:40.944 --> 33:41.910
Now, so far,
all the guard shift changes

33:41.978 --> 33:43.145
are are happening as scheduled.

33:43.213 --> 33:44.546
[ Beeping ]
What are you doing?

33:44.614 --> 33:46.248
Well, it sounds like you've got
a busy day planned.

33:46.316 --> 33:49.151
I mean, you want to make sure
this puppy is charged, right?

33:49.219 --> 33:52.321
We go at 7:00 a.m.

33:52.388 --> 33:55.624
Joey, you park the car here
on 27th.

33:55.692 --> 33:57.926
We set up here.
Guys.

33:57.994 --> 33:59.228
Nick, you cut through
the east gate...

33:59.295 --> 34:00.295
Guys,
Sam's back online.

34:00.363 --> 34:02.231
...on my command.

34:02.298 --> 34:03.932
Greg, Tommy, and I rush in
and 86 the guards.

34:04.000 --> 34:06.101
Now, the only thing standing
between us and early retirement

34:06.169 --> 34:09.137
is a couple of
$10-an-hour corpses.

34:09.205 --> 34:11.039
But that all depends on you,
Professor.

34:11.107 --> 34:14.009
There's a Miami P.D. station
a half a mile away.

34:14.077 --> 34:17.512
You don't kill those alarms,
cops show up under 30 seconds.

34:17.580 --> 34:20.549
That's 28 seconds longer
than you'll live.

34:21.451 --> 34:23.685
Well, I sure appreciate
the pep talk,

34:23.753 --> 34:25.887
but I got a bone to pick
with your plan.

34:25.955 --> 34:28.422
[ Scoffs ]
What's that?

34:28.491 --> 34:31.627
The east wall in the gem center
is a nightmare.

34:31.694 --> 34:34.362
You got your PBX switch,
you got your HVAC controls --

34:34.429 --> 34:35.864
they're all housed there.

34:35.931 --> 34:37.699
So, yes, I can kill the alarm,
but there's no guarantee

34:37.766 --> 34:39.801
that I won't set off the fire
sprinklers at the same time.

34:39.869 --> 34:41.103
So, what are you saying?

34:41.170 --> 34:42.904
Well, I'm saying
that the service entrance

34:42.972 --> 34:44.873
would be a hell of a lot easier
to break into.

34:44.940 --> 34:47.208
Here?

34:47.277 --> 34:48.877
That means we'd have to walk
all the way around the block

34:48.945 --> 34:50.978
with the gear, genius.
You want your jewels?

34:51.047 --> 34:52.447
You want to
get in and out clean?

34:52.514 --> 34:53.715
Trust me --
it'll be worth it.

34:53.783 --> 34:55.217
Get me there at 7:00,

34:55.284 --> 34:59.421
you'll be cutting through that
door at 7:05 on the button.

35:01.557 --> 35:04.559
Okay.
We do it your way.

35:04.627 --> 35:05.961
Just make sure it goes quick.

35:06.029 --> 35:09.031
Yeah, speaking of which,
we want our cash in the van.

35:09.098 --> 35:10.899
Not that I don't appreciate
your hospitality,

35:10.967 --> 35:13.135
but we go our separate ways
when the job is over.

35:13.202 --> 35:14.369
You think
I'm gonna stiff you?

35:14.437 --> 35:16.305
Well, you did
change the deal on us once.

35:16.372 --> 35:18.573
Y-you did kidnap us
at gunpoint.

35:18.641 --> 35:20.075
You shut up.
Okay.

35:22.612 --> 35:24.713
Fine.
The money will be in the van.

35:24.781 --> 35:26.882
Let's grab our gear and move.
Did he just --

35:26.949 --> 35:28.717
he just called our play.
Look.

35:28.785 --> 35:31.219
The back side of the gem center
is over here,

35:31.287 --> 35:33.955
out of sight from where they'll
park the getaway van.

35:34.023 --> 35:36.091
The van that Sam just made sure
would be stuffed with cash.

35:36.159 --> 35:39.094
Sam, you brilliant
son of a bitch.

35:42.198 --> 35:45.200
I'll never admit
that I said that.

35:45.268 --> 35:47.169
<i>Whether you're a spy</i>
<i>or a thief,</i>

35:47.236 --> 35:49.604
<i>the first priority</i>
<i>in assaulting a building</i>

35:49.672 --> 35:51.106
<i>is remaining concealed.</i>

35:51.174 --> 35:53.975
<i>If you hit the building</i>
<i>early on a Sunday morning,</i>

35:54.043 --> 35:56.912
<i>you won't have traffic</i>
<i>or pedestrians to worry about.</i>

35:56.979 --> 36:04.119
<i>And if you arrive dressed as a</i>
<i>state-contracted cleaning crew,</i>

36:04.187 --> 36:08.757
<i>anyone who does see you</i>
<i>won't give you a second look.</i>

36:08.825 --> 36:11.660
Your nest egg will be here with
your buddy when we get back.

36:11.728 --> 36:14.129
Hey, Steve, if Schmidt
even looks at you sideways,

36:14.197 --> 36:15.030
you shoot him.

36:19.102 --> 36:20.335
Let's move.

36:23.639 --> 36:25.741
Fiona: Looks like they only
left the driver in the van.

36:25.808 --> 36:27.943
Yeah, I count four
on team heist.

36:28.010 --> 36:30.445
Judging by those big-ass bags,
I'd say they're loaded for bear.

36:30.513 --> 36:33.248
Michael: Fi, you need to be
in place by 7:05.

36:33.316 --> 36:34.883
The timing
will have to be perfect.

36:34.951 --> 36:35.951
I'll be fine.

36:36.018 --> 36:37.819
Take care of yourself.

36:37.887 --> 36:39.254
You, too.

36:39.322 --> 36:42.357
Yes, and I will also
take care of myself.

36:42.425 --> 36:44.493
<i>The best way</i>
<i>to engage your enemy</i>

36:44.560 --> 36:46.528
<i>isn't always</i>
<i>with a gun in your hand.</i>

36:46.596 --> 36:48.530
[ Knock on window ] Hey, buddy.
How about a car wash, huh?

36:48.598 --> 36:49.865
<i>Come off as harmless and weak,</i>

36:49.932 --> 36:51.299
<i>and you can get close</i>
<i>to your target</i>

36:51.367 --> 36:52.834
<i>without him getting suspicious.</i>
<i>Come on, I got kids.</i>

36:52.902 --> 36:55.103
Hey, man, I said stop it.
All right? Hey!

36:55.171 --> 36:57.105
<i>And that's when you strike.</i>
<i>[ Gagging ]</i>

37:02.578 --> 37:04.913
[ Lock clicks ]

37:07.250 --> 37:09.751
Th-that was like
ninja-warrior stuff, man.

37:09.819 --> 37:12.254
You're welcome.
Grab the cash.

37:12.321 --> 37:13.622
Is he dead?

37:13.689 --> 37:16.124
No, but you'll be
if you don't hurry up and move!

37:16.192 --> 37:17.426
Sorry.

37:25.735 --> 37:27.469
Thorne:
Okay, Professor, let her rip.

37:44.120 --> 37:45.887
[ Beeping ]

37:45.955 --> 37:47.823
Come on, already.

37:50.026 --> 37:51.159
[ Whirring ]

37:51.227 --> 37:52.294
Okay,
that should do it.

37:52.361 --> 37:53.562
[ Whirring stops ]
You sure?

37:53.629 --> 37:55.297
Yeah, go ahead.
Open the door.

37:55.364 --> 37:57.332
You'll hear the sweet sound
of nothing.

37:57.400 --> 37:59.000
Let me just, uh,
pack this up.

37:59.068 --> 38:00.035
[ Grunts ]

38:00.102 --> 38:01.603
<i>For an operative,</i>

38:01.671 --> 38:05.474
<i>smuggling a gun into a mission</i>
<i>is only half the battle.</i>

38:05.541 --> 38:09.144
<i>The real trick is getting to it</i>
<i>when you need it.</i>

38:09.212 --> 38:12.647
<i>It's not the kind of thing</i>
<i>where you get a second chance,</i>

38:12.715 --> 38:16.618
<i>so when you make your move,</i>
<i>you better make it count.</i>

38:18.020 --> 38:20.689
[ Alarm beeping ]

38:20.756 --> 38:22.524
Does that sound like nothing to you?
Drop the gun!

38:22.592 --> 38:24.726
That goes for all of you.
Drop it right down.

38:24.794 --> 38:26.228
Turn around.

38:26.295 --> 38:27.662
Back up. Let's go.
Straight back.

38:27.730 --> 38:28.797
Let's go.
Same with you.

38:28.865 --> 38:30.298
Gun in the water.
Let's go!

38:30.366 --> 38:31.566
Do it,
or I put one in his head.

38:31.634 --> 38:33.568
Hurry up! Come on, move it!!
Let's go!

38:35.872 --> 38:37.706
Back to the wall.
Face the wall. Eat it.

38:39.909 --> 38:41.476
You really think
you can rip me off?

38:41.544 --> 38:43.144
I'm not
ripping anybody off, Thorne.

38:43.212 --> 38:44.813
That circuit cutter
is yours to keep,

38:44.881 --> 38:46.448
so consider our transaction
complete.

38:46.516 --> 38:47.582
[ Horn honks ]

38:47.650 --> 38:48.683
[ Tires screech ]

38:52.321 --> 38:53.355
Have a good one.

38:53.422 --> 38:54.956
What are you doing?

38:55.024 --> 38:57.559
Get back to the van!
Let's go!

38:57.627 --> 38:59.461
[ Sirens wailing ]

39:06.168 --> 39:07.435
What the hell?

39:07.503 --> 39:08.370
[ Tires screech ]

39:10.873 --> 39:11.873
No!

39:11.941 --> 39:12.974
On your knees!

39:13.042 --> 39:14.476
Hands on your head now.

39:14.544 --> 39:16.211
Officer:
Get on the ground!

39:16.279 --> 39:17.879
[ Indistinct shouting ]

39:17.947 --> 39:19.548
Son of a bitch.

39:27.619 --> 39:29.887
Okay.
I talked to my guy.

39:29.954 --> 39:32.923
He will be able to get you
to Buenos Aires.

39:32.991 --> 39:35.459
Just waiting on the passports,
but it's all taken care of.

39:35.527 --> 39:38.462
Jesse: I'd say
that calls for a toast.

39:38.530 --> 39:39.763
Yeah, none for me.
None for you?

39:39.831 --> 39:41.298
Weren't you the one
singing love ballads

39:41.366 --> 39:42.699
to this Tequila
at your warehouse?

39:42.767 --> 39:45.002
Oh, well, thank you
for offering me my own alcohol.

39:45.069 --> 39:47.471
That's -- that's generous,
but I'm not in the mood.

39:47.539 --> 39:49.740
Oh, come on, pal.
Lighten up -- one little pop.

39:49.808 --> 39:54.778
One thing that I'm not to you or
you or any of your ilk is a pal.

39:54.846 --> 39:56.280
Ouch.

39:56.347 --> 39:58.382
Hey, Schmidt, you know
what I was just thinking about?

39:58.450 --> 40:00.918
Remember that one time
when we saved your life?

40:00.985 --> 40:02.786
Oh, yeah, I do.
Oh, you know what?

40:02.854 --> 40:04.021
That doesn't count

40:04.088 --> 40:06.356
when you're the guys
who almost got me killed.

40:06.424 --> 40:08.792
You destroyed my warehouse.
I'm ripping off my clients.

40:08.860 --> 40:10.594
You guys ruined me.

40:10.662 --> 40:12.963
And you know
what I call people who do that?

40:13.031 --> 40:15.466
I call them enemies.
That's what I call them.

40:15.533 --> 40:17.334
Well, for what it's worth,
we're the kind of enemies

40:17.402 --> 40:18.836
who won't forget
what you did for us.

40:18.903 --> 40:20.637
Yeah. The kind of enemies
you can call on anytime.

40:20.705 --> 40:22.306
Seriously, man.
Thank you.

40:23.641 --> 40:26.076
Okay, fine. I'll do --
I'll do your dumb toast,

40:26.144 --> 40:27.544
but only
because I cannot wait

40:27.612 --> 40:30.113
for all of you to get
the hell out of my country.

40:30.181 --> 40:31.548
Well, we'll take it.

40:31.616 --> 40:32.883
[ Glasses clink ]

40:32.951 --> 40:34.151
Here's to
seeing the world.

40:34.219 --> 40:36.887
May the skin of your bum
never cover a drum.

40:36.955 --> 40:38.555
Right.

40:41.059 --> 40:44.261
<i>Leaving signals in public</i>
<i>is a time-honored way</i>

40:44.329 --> 40:46.830
<i>for spies to communicate</i>
<i>in the field.</i>

40:46.898 --> 40:48.298
<i>It's reliable and easy,</i>

40:48.366 --> 40:50.400
<i>but the downside is you have to</i>
<i>check for messages</i>

40:50.468 --> 40:51.668
<i>on a constant basis.</i>

40:51.736 --> 40:53.070
Fiona: Michael,
the bench -- green "X."

40:53.137 --> 40:54.738
<i>And if you see one,</i>

40:54.806 --> 40:56.840
<i>you have to hurry to a rally</i>
<i>point as fast as you can...</i>

40:56.908 --> 40:58.141
[ Tires squeal ]

40:58.209 --> 41:01.645
<i>...and hope</i>
<i>that it's not too late.</i>

41:02.507 --> 41:03.719
Mom,
is everything all right?

41:03.720 --> 41:05.020
We saw the signal.
No.

41:05.088 --> 41:06.455
Everything isn't all right.
Fiona: What happened?

41:06.522 --> 41:07.656
Did the transfers --

41:07.724 --> 41:09.191
No, no,
the transfers are fine.

41:09.258 --> 41:10.759
But Riley has Barry.

41:10.827 --> 41:13.695
And she knows I'm the one
who put him up to it.

41:13.763 --> 41:15.664
Can she prove ?
[ Sighs ]

41:15.732 --> 41:18.133
She has DNA -- something.
I don't know.

41:18.201 --> 41:19.768
She's coming after me now.

41:19.836 --> 41:21.503
I'm so sorry, mom.

41:21.571 --> 41:23.004
[ Crying ]
It doesn't matter.

41:23.072 --> 41:24.272
I'm really,
really sorry.

41:24.340 --> 41:25.340
It's all right.

41:25.408 --> 41:26.808
You're doing
the best you can, honey.

41:26.876 --> 41:28.944
I'll find
a place to live.

41:29.011 --> 41:31.880
I've got, um...I've got
a friend from high school.

41:31.948 --> 41:34.416
I mean, I haven't...
talked to her in years,

41:34.484 --> 41:35.517
but I could
probably stay there.

41:35.585 --> 41:38.220
Madeline,
you can't stay in Miami.

41:38.287 --> 41:39.621
Well, what am I
supposed to do?!

41:42.258 --> 41:43.291
You'll come with us.

41:43.359 --> 41:44.993
We're already
having cover I.D.s made.

41:45.061 --> 41:46.495
We'll make one more.

41:46.562 --> 41:48.630
Michael,
do I look like somebody

41:48.698 --> 41:50.866
who's ready for a life
on the run?

41:50.933 --> 41:52.634
Please, Mom.

41:52.702 --> 41:53.902
I need you
to do this.

41:53.970 --> 41:55.137
Why?

41:55.204 --> 41:57.205
'Cause I promised Sam
I would make this right,

41:57.273 --> 42:01.076
and I can't do that
with you in prison.

42:01.144 --> 42:04.279
Because you're the only family
I have left.

42:13.556 --> 42:16.525
[ Sighs, sniffles ]

42:16.592 --> 42:19.461
Well, I'm not
going anywhere cold.

42:22.198 --> 42:23.265
I mean it.

42:23.332 --> 42:25.834
Deal.

